                  README

This java package shows how to write a Java client to talk to TickTockDB.

The java program, HttpClientExample, writes two data points to TickTockDB using HTTP. It then queries the result to verify that the data points have been written into TickTockDB.

Compile:
ylin30@yi-IdeaPad:~/ticktock/api-examples/java$ mvn package assembly:single

Run:
ylin30@yi-IdeaPad:~/ticktock/api-examples/java$ java -cp target/client-sample-0.1-jar-with-dependencies.jar com.ticktock.HttpClientExample 192.168.1.34 6189

